description:
Role and Job Duties:

The Institute is in the process of recruiting a Chief Operating Officer (COO). In the interim, the post of Deputy COO will serve as the leading administrator of the Secretariat, Registrar of Architect’s Registration Board (ARB) and supporting team of the Institute. The duties include but not limited to:

Manage, monitor and responsible for the HKIA Secretariat (currently around 27 staff in Hong Kong and 1 in Beijing) to ensure smooth and efficient daily operation;  
Implement effective work plans for the delivery of various events/programmes within time and budget constraints;
Works collaboratively to develop and/or improve systems, processes, controls and procedures;
Assist Council to ensure and maintain good governance and responsive service to the members;
Assist the Board in determining the long-term strategic direction in close alignment with the Institute’s mission, vision and values;
Maintain good contact with government, business corporations, NGOs, allied professional bodies, media, all other related stakeholders and the general public of the community;
Attend functions and events on behalf of the Institute and perform duties designated by Council and Office Bearers; 
Serve as the Registrar of the Architects Registration Board HKSAR and be responsible for the administrative duties under the Architects Registration Ordinance;
Serve as the Registrar of HKIA and be responsible for the administrative duties under the Operation Manual of the institute;
Provides timely, accurate and complete reports on the operating condition of the Institute;
To act as the legal person (法人) of Office in Beijing;
Perform any other duties as assigned by Office Bearers and Council from time to time;
DCOO will report directly to the Council and OB for all matters of HKIA.  
Skills Required:

Possess basic knowledge of employment law and legal compliance
Experience in financial and accounting management
Working knowledge of IT/Business infrastructure
Outstanding organizational and leadership abilities
Aptitude in decision-making and problem-solving
Presentable and with excellent communication and interpersonal skills
Experience in government funding and tender process will be a plus
Bachelor degree in business administration or relevant field; or more than 15 years’ working experience at Senior Management level of reputable organization; MBA is a plus      
Contract Terms and Eligibility:


It is a temporary post with 9 months contract period. The period may be extended subject to operation needs. Remuneration package will be offered to the right candidate.

Interested applicants, please send full resume with career history, last and expected salary to HKIA Secretariat by clicking “Apply Now”.  Deadline for application is 10th Jan 2022.

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to attend written test and interview. All personal data collected will be strictly kept confidential and for recruitment-related purpose only.

A Hong Kong based NGO which provides choral and artistic training to children, with frequent performances locally and overseas. Vacancy now arises for a General Manager with the following duties:

To lead the administrative staff in daily operation and liaison with outside parties;
To assist the Honorary Treasurer in preparing the budget;
To assist the Music Director in administration of the music and artistic staff, organizes choir practices and performances;
To carry out instructions of the Board of Directors, to report to the Board and to coordinate between the Board and the Music Director.

 Qualifications:

University degree or above, Arts Management or related disciplines would be an advantage;
At least 8 years’ managerial experience;
Strong communication skill in Cantonese, Putonghua and English;
Relevant work experience in management of tutors and members in artistic organization would be an advantage.
Interested candidates, please contact us at 37059667 for company details before applying.
